<div id="review_2292840766" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2292840766" />
    <a title="Doubledf99.99" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/19135352-doubledf99-99"><img alt="Doubledf99.99" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1388397054p2/19135352.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2292840766?book_show_action=true">Feb 19, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Doubledf99.99" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Doubledf99.99" href="/user/show/19135352-doubledf99-99">Doubledf99.99</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/20471037-tales-of-nev-r-on">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/19135352-doubledf99-99?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/19135352-doubledf99-99?shelf=fantasy-sword-and-sorcery">fantasy-sword-and-sorcery</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2292840766" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8735565026263997736">I thought this would be a nice light fantasy read, however I was proven wrong from the get go. Delany creates a ancient world that puts one to thinking, and a world that is starting to civilize, money making an appearance over barter, first writings, new inventions and improved inventions, with all this the world is still most brutal. There are Dragons. And women are at the forefront. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


