        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer127216985" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14868928142562610914">Okay. God. Incredible fantasy that investigates what fantasy actually is, and makes the homoeroticism of sword &amp; sorcery finally explicit, and deals with race, slavery, rebellion, and s/m, and tons of stuff about gender and relation of gender oppression to money, and the relation of general oppression to money, and a bunch of other shit. Jesus, so brill. And there is more to the series - this collects the first 5 stories and there are other novels and novellas and stuff to follow. Totally thrill</span>
  <span id="freeText14868928142562610914" style="display:none">Okay. God. Incredible fantasy that investigates what fantasy actually is, and makes the homoeroticism of sword &amp; sorcery finally explicit, and deals with race, slavery, rebellion, and s/m, and tons of stuff about gender and relation of gender oppression to money, and the relation of general oppression to money, and a bunch of other shit. Jesus, so brill. And there is more to the series - this collects the first 5 stories and there are other novels and novellas and stuff to follow. Totally thrilling. From the preface that discusses Delany's work in third person but is "written by" a fictional character later in the series, this shit is complex. There were passages I had to read repeatedly, both because they were hard but they also were thrilling and dialectical and felt important. Loved it. </span>
  <a data-text-id="14868928142562610914" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


